<section class="section-block">
	<h2>SMS-enable any number — even one you didn't get from us</h2>
	<p>If you (or your customer) own a phone number on a different carrier, VoiceTel can SMS-enable it. Sign a Letter of Authorization, we handle the carrier coordination, and the number stays where it is for voice. Useful when a customer can't move their voice service but wants application messaging on the same DID.</p>
</section>

<section class="section-block faq-block">
	<h2>Messaging FAQ</h2>
	<details class="faq-item">
		<summary>Does VoiceTel handle A2P 10DLC?</summary>
		<p>Yes. VoiceTel supports A2P 10DLC workflows. Registration, vetting, campaign approval, fees, and ownership are described precisely in onboarding and service terms. The 10DLC application and any associated fees are the sole responsibility of the customer.</p>
	</details>
	<details class="faq-item">
		<summary>Are carrier fees included?</summary>
		<p>Carrier pass-through fees are listed separately from base message prices unless pricing data explicitly includes them.</p>
	</details>
	<details class="faq-item">
		<summary>Can high-volume senders get dedicated SMPP binds for increased capacity?</summary>
		<p>Yes. Speak with your messaging specialist to discuss your use case.</p>
	</details>
	<details class="faq-item">
		<summary>Can VoiceTel handle traffic for phone numbers it doesn't own?</summary>
		<p>Yes. With a Letter of Authorization (LOA), we can SMS-enable any phone number.</p>
	</details>
	<details class="faq-item">
		<summary>Who pays for compliance?</summary>
		<p>10DLC brand registration, campaign filing, and any associated fees are the sole responsibility of the customer. VoiceTel supports A2P 10DLC workflows as the messaging transport — registration, vetting, campaign approval, fees, and ownership are described precisely in onboarding and service terms.</p>
	</details>
</section>

